issue.title: Uploading CRM Extensions not working. Requires "fetch" that can't be there.
issue.body:
## Description and Context
Uploading CRM UI Extension [examples](https://github.com/HubSpot/ui-extensions-examples) won't pass the build tests anymore. 

`hs project upload --account=demo
Failed to upload crm-card project files to demo (20714910)
[ERROR] The post in account 20714910 was bad. The JSON in the file '/app/extensions/example-card.json' doesn't match the associated scheme. Correct and/or add values to all relevant fields and try again.
- $.data.fetch: is missing but it is required`

If I put "fetch" to the card.json as requested, the card will try to fetch layout from that "crm-card" appFunction endpoint and that is not the case we want to achieve when creating react extensions.

`"fetch": {
    "targetFunction": "crm-card",
    "objectTypes": [
      {
        "name": "deals",
        "propertiesToSend": ["dealname"]
      }
    ]
  }`

Tried this with versions 4.1.7 and 5.0.1. 

![Näyttökuva 2023-10-26 kello 14 45 32](https://github.com/HubSpot/hubspot-cli/assets/2910861/880c00df-436a-4768-b42e-cb19742c766c)

### Steps to reproduce
1. git clone https://github.com/HubSpot/ui-extensions-examples.git
3. cd ui-extensions-examples/contact-duplicate
4. hs project upload (+ name and location selection as normally)



PS. I'm not sure if this is a cli problem or more of a server-side issue. Please advise where this should be directed if it does not belong here. And please let me know if I have misunderstood this issue.

pull_request.title: Use local dev lib config
pull_request.body:
## Description and Context
This switches the CLI from using `@hubspot/cli-lib` for `config` to using `@hubspot/local-dev-lib`. The config module is functionally identical between both, so everything should behave exactly the same. Once this PR is merged, we'll be able to start porting everything else over to `local-dev-lib

## TODO
* This PR will need to be merged and released in tandem with this `cli-lib` PR https://github.com/HubSpot/cli-lib/pull/22
As well as a PR for the VSCode extension
* It would probably be good to stress test this pretty thoroughly before doing a full release.

## Who to Notify
@brandenrodgers

issue.title: Added access token authentication
issue.body:
## Description and Context
Since usage of `ApiKey` will be soon deprecated, I've added a custom auth type for using Access Keys from Private Apps. This is necessary to still use the hubspot cli on any CI/CD pipelines. Sample configuration would be:
```
portals:
  - name: ACCESSTOKEN
    portalId: 4444
    authType: accesstoken 
    accessToken: fakeAccessToken  

```

<!-- Provide a summary of what has changed -->
<!-- Provide links to relevant discussions or documentation to promote understanding and addressing this PR -->
<!-- Describe any packages you'd like to add and the reasons why. -->

## Screenshots

## TODO

- Update `init` command to fully support and configure `accesstoken` auth type
- Update necessary documentations

## Who to Notify

comment.body:
@dpritos - Thank you so much for providing that insight.

I don't appear to be able to get this working?

My steps are as follows
1. Generate a `Private App Token`
    - https://developers.hubspot.com/docs/api/private-apps
1. Install Hubspot CLI
    - `npm install -g @hubspot/cli`
1. Set Portal ID
    - `export HUBSPOT_PORTAL_ID="REDACTED"`
1. Set `Private App Token` as `HUBSPOT_ACCESS_TOKEN`
    - `export HUBSPOT_ACCESS_TOKEN="PRIVATE_APP_TOKEN"
1. Perform Upload
    -  `hs upload --use-env build REDACTED`

However, when I do this I receive
```
[ERROR] Error while retrieving new access token: Failed to sign refresh token because refresh token was malformed and could not be decoded. Generate a new refresh token and try again.
```

Are you using a `Private App Token` to authenticate? If not, how are you achieving your authentication solution?

pull_request.title: Swap cli-lib 'text' dep for local-dev-lib version
pull_request.body:
## Description and Context
See https://git.hubteam.com/HubSpot/hubspot-cli-issues/issues/476

This adds `@hubspot/local-dev-lib` as a dependancy to the CLI and imports its version of `text` in places where the `cli-lib` version was being used. `text` is a really simple function, so figured this would be a good way to test the waters before swapping any other deps

## TODO

- [ ] Publish `v1.0.0` of `@hubspot/local-dev-lib`
- [ ] Update the dependency here

## Who to Notify

pull_request.title: Upgrade to node 18
pull_request.body:
## Description and Context
This upgrades the CLI and related packages to node version 18. Node version 16 was deprecated in september, and `hubspot-local-dev-lib` uses node 18 so we'll need to upgrade before we can start using it. This may require a major release.

## Who to Notify
